1️⃣ @RequestMapping

@RequestMapping anedi base URL set cheyadaniki use chestam.
Example:

@RestController
@RequestMapping("/student")
public class StudentController {

}

Meaning:

/student → base URL

So inside methods:

/student/all
/student/name
/student/id

@RequestMapping can be used at both class level and method level.
Class level → base URL
Method level → specific endpoint mapping

2️⃣ @GetMapping

GET request ante data fetch cheyadaniki.

Example:

@GetMapping("/hello")
public String hello() {
    return "Hello Spring Boot";
}

Browser lo call:

http://localhost:8080/hello
🟢 Example – Student Controller

Create new controller:

com.prince.firstApp.controller

Class name:

StudentController

Code:

package com.prince.firstApp.controller;

import org.springframework.web.bind.annotation.GetMapping;
import org.springframework.web.bind.annotation.RestController;
import org.springframework.web.bind.annotation.RequestMapping;

@RestController
@RequestMapping("/student")
public class StudentController {

    @GetMapping("/name")
    public String studentName() {
        return "Student name is Hemanth";
    }

    @GetMapping("/course")
    public String studentCourse() {
        return "Student is learning Spring Boot";
    }

}
🧪 Browser Testing

Try these:

http://localhost:8080/student/name
http://localhost:8080/student/course

3️⃣ @PathVariable (Very Important)

URL lo value pass cheyadaniki use chestam.

Example URL:

/student/101

Code:

@GetMapping("/{id}")
public String getStudent(@PathVariable int id) {
    return "Student ID is " + id;
}

Browser:

http://localhost:8080/student/101

Output:

Student ID is 101


4️⃣ @RequestParam

